# Working documents live in `.apm/`

When creating or updating **working material** for this application—plans, rough design notes, scratch specifications, implementation drafts, and anything used to “work things out” before it is product truth—**write under `.apm/`** (repo root), e.g. `.apm/plan-feature-foo.md`.

**Do not** place those files under `docs/` **unless the user explicitly says otherwise** (e.g. “put this in docs” or “promote to SRS”).

**Keep in `docs/`** without asking each time: stable references the team treats as published—`Application-SRS.md`, `Application-Spec.md`, `BACKLOG.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `DATABASE_SCHEMA.md`, `AI_ENVIRONMENT.md`, external-facing templates, etc.

After a plan stabilizes, **merge** the substance into the appropriate `docs/*` (and contracts) in a separate step—the working copy can stay in `.apm/` or be archived.

Note: `.apm/` is gitignored; working docs are local unless you add narrow git exceptions.
